                    <comment id="12601333" author="hossman" created="Sat, 31 May 2008 04:12:22 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;FWIW: I included it originally because i&apos;ve definitely seen value in the past when you can look at an artifact and ask &quot;who built this? where did it come from?&quot; ... maybe not so much for official releases but i&apos;ve been in enough positions where organizations build their own artifacts from source and later you want to know who built it so you can double check with them how they did it (because you think they screwed something up)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I believe maven actually forcibly puts the build user in every manifest file, so it&apos;s not like we were in bleeding edge territory or anything.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12601336" author="cutting" created="Sat, 31 May 2008 04:32:29 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I too always felt this a feature, albeit a minor one.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
